Traffic police officers had pulled over a driver on the M5 in Gloucesteshire . 
  They were standing on the hard shoulder when a caravan sped past with its back window open . 
  The two officers spotted the window was open and had to dive out of the way with seconds to spare . 
  The caravan narrowly missed the officers and narrowly missed a workman . 
  The driver was unaware that the window had opened and was unaware he was speeding . 
 